Package game

Class Player

java.lang.Object
game.Polygon
game.Player
All Implemented Interfaces:
KeyListener, EventListener
public class Player extends Polygon implements KeyListener
The Player class extends Polygon and is the only element of Geometry Dash which the player has control of. It is a 20x20 pixel square and the only input is to jump. There is only one Player object for every Level object.
Author:
Justin Chai

  • Constructor Details

    • Player

      public Player()
      Sole constructor. Invokes the Polygon constructor to make a 20x20 square on the on the ground at x = 100. vel = 0, isFalling = false, and canJump = true.

  • Method Details

    • paint

      public void paint(Graphics brush)
      Draws the Player object in the GeometryDash canvas. Uses the Polygon method getPoints() and the Graphics object parameter to draw the player. After drawing the object, it then calls the move method.
      Parameters:
      brush - Graphics object with which the current object is drawn.
      See Also:
      • Graphics.fillPolygon(int[], int[], int)
      • Polygon.move()
